snippet.textDisplay:
Since I was in 5th grade I had a bad time. In 10th and 11th grade, it was ok, because my old bullies were gone. I'm currently in 12th grade and I'm struggling with many anxieties. My biggest fear are silent rooms with people in it because I always get hungry in these situations and have to fear that my stomach is making noises.

I hate tests because whatever I try, no matter how much I eat during these super long tests I'm always hungry. That new problem exists since a month. My other problems started in September. And even if I already wasn't happy in the 11th grade, it's even worse now. I have so many fears...I also can only sit on one specific spot to be able to focus on the test.

And tomorrow is the next test, almost 3 hours and on Friday there will be an English test for almost 4 hours. And I still have 12 tests to go for the next two or 3 months. I just don't know how I'll survive that... It seems impossible to me. Every day I cry myself to sleep and I'd like to get some help in a clinic because my problems are taking over my life. But I would never ask my parents if they would help me by doing that.

Seriously, I have almost no friends and I usually don't leave the house. I miss my old life. And there's still a year to go for me until I'm finished with school.
I know everyone will say 'Wtf your problems aren't reap problems'
But you don't know me and my reality and what I've gone through the years before. I wish I was someone else.

snippet.textDisplay: Middle school sucked. It was the worst. I was the girl worth the really poofy brown hair, acne, glasses and braces who wanted so badly to be pretty and have friends but ended up spending all of her time alone in the library or mercilessly bullied. I hated who I was and ended up dealing with a lot of mental health issues by suppressing them and hating myself for having them. Thinking back to that kid that I was absolutely breaks my heart.

snippet.textDisplay: I love this video because it wasn't just for entertainment purposes like yeah the idea of recreating past photos is something nostalgic, but I think it allowed the Try Guys to somehow dig deeper and compare their growth back then to now. They were all kind of saying how they weren't considered as the "coolest" people in middle school but looking at them now, they're so accepting of their past. Them talking about their struggle resonates with a lot of us too but I guess I don't have to worry so much about it because they're living examples of how things will get better.

snippet.textDisplay:
My preteens were great overall except my parents took me out of public school to homeschool me after elementary. I thank god that in my neighborhood I had 5 (1 of which who my next door neighbor was homeschooled as well) friends my age that are still my friends today.

If I didn’t have that I feel I would’ve been in a much different place than I am now.

I don’t have a problem with homeschooling, but damn it really takes you away from other kids your age.

snippet.textDisplay:
I remember when I got caught selling candy, soda and artwork and my grade principal called my mom. They told her I was "soliciting sales" and over speakerphone my mom goes
My Mom: "Soliciting sales?! Was she selling drugs!?"
My principal: "Uhh No Mis..."
My Mom: "Was selling sex!?"(fyi she didn't say sex)
My Principal: "GOD NO! She was selling candy and snack cakes to fellow students."
Me: "And 2 teachers.😏"
My Mom: "I know damn well you don't call me about no candy and Little Debbie's...?" hangs up phone
My Principal: 😕 "Well..."
I continue to sell candy, snacks and juices because my mom was dating a guy whose family owned 2 candy stores so I stayed well stocked. Lol
